 management  international wealth management iwm basic banking product management   length  months  start date by arrangement workplace zurich academic qualification at least four completed semesters at a university or university of applied sciences preferably in economics or engineering or equivalent  your benefitsinternational working environment work in a swiss corporation with an international outlook and cultural diversity shadowing days opportunity to gain insight into other areas of the bank and expand your knowledge internship events chance to get to know other interns make new contacts across different areas and build up a network at various events fulltime perspective possibility of a position in the career start program after successfully completing the internship and finishing your studies your tasks you support the iwm basic banking product management team including the setup of the governance around the newly created iwm product and pricing committeeyou are actively involved in a dynamic team that is part of the iwm coo business areayou perform a variety of tasks in the areas of market and product analyses the revision of the iwm basic banking product offering as well as the preparation of the monthly iwm product and pricing committee  you undertake demanding analyses in order to prepare proposals on how to further develop iwm’s basic banking product landscapeyou gain an indepth insight into the development and management of product and pricing for basic banking productsyou actively collaborate in the daily tasks of a product manageryou are involved in the development of presentations for our senior managementyou coordinate various stakeholders in advance of the monthly iwm iwm product and pricing committee your profile are you a structured and dynamic person with a high level of autonomycan the quality of your work meet high standards and do you take lastminute schedule changes in stridedo you like a generalist role and proactively meet challengesare 