ople company overview credit suisse international together with its subsidiaries provides overthecounter otc derivative products worldwide it operates through six segments global markets apac investment banking  capital markets swiss universal bank international wealth management and strategic resolution unit it provides a range of interest rate currency equity and creditrelated otc derivatives and various securitized products the company offers a suite of products and services including securities sales trading and execution and investment research to financial institutions corporations and governments as well as institutional investors such as pension and hedge funds it also provide credit suisse international together with its subsidiaries provides overthecounter otc derivative products worldwide it operates through six segments global markets apac investment banking  capital markets swiss universal bank international wealth management and strategic resolution unit it provides a range of interest rate currency equity and creditrelated otc derivatives and various securitized products the company offers a suite of products and services including securities sales trading and execution and investment research to financial institutions corporations and governments as well as institutional investors such as pension and hedge funds it also provides advisory services on various aspects of corporate sales and restructurings divestitures and takeover defense strategies ma and spinoffs debt and equity underwriting of public offerings and private placements and related derivative transactions in addition the company offers equities and fixed income sales and trading services a range of debt and equity securities and financing for corporate sovereign and institutional clients further it provides clients sales and trading services in foreign exchange products as well as engages in local market currency trading activities the company was incorporated in  and is based in london 